Add Calculated Insights to a Data Graph

You can include calculated insights in a data graph as long as they’re based on a data model object (DMO) that’s also included in the data graph. The DMO’s primary key field must be configured as a dimension on the calculated insight object (CIO).

Next to the DMO name, click the “+” icon and select a related CIO. In the object picker, CIOs are denoted with the (Data Graph) icon.
Select dimensions and measures on the Fields tab.
EXAMPLE JSON Data: This data graph JSON shows a calculated insight with two dimensions and two measures. Unified Individual is the primary DMO, and one of the dimensions on the calculated insight is the primary key field on Unified Individual DMO.
